Religious leader Shepherd Bushiri and his wife Mary are back to the Pretoria Magistrates court. Both are facing charges of fraud, theft and money laundering. JOHANNESBURG - Self-proclaimed Prophet Shepherd Bushiri, his wife Mary, and three others are expected to find out if they will be released on bail. Earlier this week Magistrate Thandi Theledi postponed the matter, saying she can only give it full attention on Friday. READ: Bushiri bail judgment postponed to Friday The five have been in custody since Tuesday, last week. They are facing charges of fraud, theft, and money laundering to the value of over R100-million.